# Foundry CI Roadmap

This document outlines the phased implementation plan for Foundry CI capabilities.

## Phase 1: Core CI Infrastructure

Foundational CI capabilities that compose existing CI primitives into Workshop-aware experiences.

| Item | Description | Dependencies |
|------|-------------|--------------|
| **Test Runners** | Standardized test execution with Workshop-scoped configuration | GitHub Actions adapter |
| **Test Reports** | Unified test result aggregation across code repos | Quality Service |
| **Evidence Packs** | Structured collection of build evidence (tests, coverage, security scans) | Test Reports |

### Evidence Packs

Evidence Packs aggregate proof artifacts for release readiness:
- Test results (unit, integration, e2e)
- Coverage reports
- Security scan findings
- Static analysis results
- Performance benchmarks
- Compliance attestations

Evidence Packs are attached to Release Intents and reviewed before release approval.

## Phase 2: Quality Intelligence

Build quality measurement and trend analysis.

| Item | Description | Dependencies |
|------|-------------|--------------|
| **BQI (Build Quality Indicators)** | Composite metrics for build health | Test Reports, Evidence Packs |
| **Tech Debt Tracking** | Integration with debt registers for automated detection | Governance module |
| **Quality Thresholds** | Configurable gates based on BQI scores | BQI |

### Build Quality Indicators (BQI)

BQI provides a single score representing build health:
- Test pass rate (weighted by criticality)
- Code coverage (weighted by change scope)
- Security findings (weighted by severity)
- Static analysis issues (weighted by category)
- Build time and stability

BQI thresholds are configured at Workshop and Workbench levels.

## Phase 3: Agentic Quality Gates

Agent-powered quality evaluation and automated remediation.

| Item | Description | Dependencies |
|------|-------------|--------------|
| **Agentic Quality Gates** | Trained Agents evaluate changes against quality criteria | Agent Fabric, BQI |
| **Crowd-sourced Skills** | Community skills for specialized quality checks | Skill Registry |
| **Project-Template-Specific Triggers** | Quality gates customized per project type | Work Catalog |

### Agentic Quality Gates

Quality gates can invoke Trained Agents for:
- Security vulnerability triage and fix suggestions
- Test generation for uncovered code paths
- Documentation validation
- Breaking change detection
- Performance regression analysis

## Phase 4: Integration Enhancements

Extended integrations with external tools and communication platforms.

| Item | Description | Dependencies |
|------|-------------|--------------|
| **MS Teams Integration** | CI notifications and status via Workspace Settings | Workspace Settings |
| **TestRail Integration** | Test suite synchronization with release pipelines | Quality Service |
| **Jira Integration** | Automated issue creation from CI failures | Work Repository |

### TestRail Test Suite Support

Release pipelines can:
- Execute TestRail test runs as part of CI
- Sync results back to TestRail
- Include TestRail results in Evidence Packs
- Gate releases on TestRail test plan completion

## Implementation Notes

- CI agents use a **separate harness** from WO Runtime agents — see [ci-agent-architecture.md](../ci-agent-architecture.md)
- All CI features respect Workshop-scoped configuration
- Quality metrics flow to Governance module for compliance reporting
- Integration with [Validation module](../../../management/platform-developer-guide/validation/README.md) for pre-merge gates (Foundry-scope config only)